WEBVTT

1
00:00:07.048 --> 00:00:09.926
[piano playing]

2
00:00:16.975 --> 00:00:18.977
[tempo increases]

3
00:00:20.000 --> 00:00:26.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

4
00:00:47.088 --> 00:00:49.424
[thunder rumbling]

5
00:00:57.724 --> 00:00:59.059
[sighs heavily]

6
00:01:05.148 --> 00:01:07.358
[clock ticking]

7
00:01:11.613 --> 00:01:12.739
[lock screen clicks]

8
00:01:13.239 --> 00:01:14.324
[sighs]

9
00:01:18.745 --> 00:01:20.121
[outbound text swooshes]

10
00:01:25.752 --> 00:01:27.754
[phone ringing]

11
00:01:27.837 --> 00:01:29.255
- [voicemail beeps]
- [woman] Jamal.

12
00:01:30.048 --> 00:01:31.549
God damn it. Where are you?

13
00:01:31.633 --> 00:01:33.510
I've sent you four texts. no. five.

14
00:01:33.593 --> 00:01:35.011
You can't text me back?

15
00:01:35.261 --> 00:01:36.262
Call me.

16
00:01:40.642 --> 00:01:43.228
- [ringing]
- [voicemail beeps]

17
00:01:43.353 --> 00:01:46.689
<i>It's me again. Honey. I'm sorry. I...</i>

18
00:01:48.149 --> 00:01:50.401
I'm sorry. I-I didn't mean to get angry.

19
00:01:50.485 --> 00:01:51.903
Call me. please.

20
00:01:53.738 --> 00:01:55.615
[thunder crashes]

21
00:01:59.536 --> 00:02:01.371
[phone ringing in the distance]

22
00:02:10.296 --> 00:02:11.422
[lock screen clicks]

23
00:02:21.766 --> 00:02:24.102
- [ringing]
- [sighs]

24
00:02:26.437 --> 00:02:28.916
- [male voice] <i>Hello. Hey. it's Jeffrey.</i>
- Hi. this is... [scoffs]

25
00:02:28.940 --> 00:02:30.066
- Shit.
<i>- Leave a message.</i>

26
00:02:30.150 --> 00:02:31.276
<i>and I'll get back to you.</i>

27
00:02:31.359 --> 00:02:32.359
[beeps]

28
00:02:32.402 --> 00:02:35.155
Jeffrey. this is Jamal's mother.

29
00:02:35.238 --> 00:02:37.073
It's. uh... Tuesday...

30
00:02:37.157 --> 00:02:39.742
No. Wednesday night... m-morning. Um...

31
00:02:39.826 --> 00:02:40.952
[sighs]

32
00:02:42.036 --> 00:02:43.371
I'm looking for Jamal.

33
00:02:43.454 --> 00:02:45.748
He hasn't come home. and I...

34
00:02:45.832 --> 00:02:47.417
I thought he might be with you.

35
00:02:47.500 --> 00:02:51.254
I-I'm sorry to bother you.
or. you know. call so early. but...

36
00:02:51.337 --> 00:02:52.337
[door clicks]

37
00:02:52.380 --> 00:02:56.050
If you get this message and he's with you.
can you please have him call me?

38
00:02:56.134 --> 00:02:58.011
- My number is 305...
- [door slams]

39
00:02:58.094 --> 00:03:00.555
Well. it's on your...
Oh. God. okay. hold on.

40
00:03:00.638 --> 00:03:06.102
Just in case. no. um. 305-468-5900.

41
00:03:07.687 --> 00:03:08.687
Okay.

42
00:03:08.813 --> 00:03:10.356
- Sorry.
- So I checked.

43
00:03:10.815 --> 00:03:12.650
like you asked.
and the car does show up.

44
00:03:12.734 --> 00:03:14.527
- Yeah.
- It shows up in the system.

45
00:03:14.611 --> 00:03:16.571
- Shows...
- That's all we really know right now.

46
00:03:17.113 --> 00:03:20.116
- Show... Shows up how?
- It just shows up. as. you know.

47
00:03:22.535 --> 00:03:25.538
What's... How does it end up coming
to the attention of. you know...

48
00:03:25.622 --> 00:03:28.249
Oh. it just was logged in. you know.
from an incident.

49
00:03:28.333 --> 00:03:30.293
It could've been ticketed.
could've been towed...

50
00:03:30.376 --> 00:03:32.754
But Jamal. my son. he was driving it.
and he...

51
00:03:32.837 --> 00:03:35.317
I thought you told me you weren't
sure whether or not he was...

52
00:03:35.381 --> 00:03:36.466
Well. yeah. Yes. Okay.

53
00:03:36.549 --> 00:03:38.259
yeah. I didn't see him drive away in it.

54
00:03:38.343 --> 00:03:41.512
I did not actually see him get
in the car. Correct.

55
00:03:41.596 --> 00:03:43.765
But the car's not in our driveway.

56
00:03:44.140 --> 00:03:45.940
He's been gone
since eight o'clock last night.

57
00:03:45.975 --> 00:03:48.269
Going on eight... I mean. nine hours.

58
00:03:48.353 --> 00:03:50.021
- He's usually home at midnight.
- Right.

59
00:03:50.104 --> 00:03:51.481
He never came home.

60
00:03:52.190 --> 00:03:53.608
And when I called the police.

61
00:03:53.691 --> 00:03:55.777
they said something happened
to the car and...

62
00:03:55.860 --> 00:03:57.528
I thought you told me they said it was...

63
00:03:57.612 --> 00:03:58.905
Hold on. I wrote it down.

64
00:04:00.240 --> 00:04:01.574
[officer sighs]

65
00:04:04.327 --> 00:04:07.497
Okay. um. "An incident."
[stammering] I. um...

66
00:04:07.580 --> 00:04:09.975
That's what she said. an incident.
"Identified in an incident."

67
00:04:09.999 --> 00:04:12.877
Yes. I understand.
And. listen. I'm really very sorr...

68
00:04:12.961 --> 00:04:14.462
I'm sure that he's gonna turn up.

69
00:04:14.545 --> 00:04:18.383
And you've already told me that you're not
the registered owner of the vehicle.

70
00:04:18.466 --> 00:04:19.467
So. I-I mean...

71
00:04:19.550 --> 00:04:21.779
I told you I would verify
the vehicle information anyway.

72
00:04:21.803 --> 00:04:23.805
And I did that. okay?

73
00:04:25.890 --> 00:04:27.183
He has work.

74
00:04:28.393 --> 00:04:30.478
- Sorry?
- Well. an internship.

75
00:04:31.020 --> 00:04:33.189
Jamal. he has a very prestigious...

76
00:04:34.315 --> 00:04:36.192
He has some place to be this morning.

77
00:04:36.276 --> 00:04:37.694
- Sure.
- This isn't like him.

78
00:04:37.777 --> 00:04:38.611
- Ma'am...
- Look.

79
00:04:38.695 --> 00:04:41.197
can't you do a missing persons report
or something?

80
00:04:41.281 --> 00:04:42.991
Not for 48 hours. no.

81
00:04:43.074 --> 00:04:45.451
- Or if there's evidence of. you know...
- Foul play.

82
00:04:45.535 --> 00:04:47.870
We don't really use that term.
That's the movies.

83
00:04:47.954 --> 00:04:49.289
Okay. Something bad. Whatever.

84
00:04:49.372 --> 00:04:51.207
- Right.
- He hasn't come home.

85
00:04:52.125 --> 00:04:53.668
[sighs]

86
00:04:55.211 --> 00:04:57.463
He's a responsible kid.

87
00:04:57.547 --> 00:04:59.799
- His car could have been stolen.
- We don't know that.

88
00:04:59.882 --> 00:05:01.134
- He's missing!
- Okay.

89
00:05:01.217 --> 00:05:02.135
Isn't that enough?

90
00:05:02.218 --> 00:05:05.430
Look. he's... [scoffs] He's 16. 17.

91
00:05:05.513 --> 00:05:07.056
Just turned 18.

92
00:05:07.140 --> 00:05:09.642
Oh! Oh. so he's just about
to graduate high school?

93
00:05:10.685 --> 00:05:12.729
- Yeah.
- So...

94
00:05:12.812 --> 00:05:14.689
- So. what?
- So he's probably...

95
00:05:15.273 --> 00:05:16.399
out on South Beach

96
00:05:16.482 --> 00:05:19.277
or. you know. well. I know
you probably don't want to hear this.

97
00:05:19.360 --> 00:05:20.862
but hanging out with some girl.

98
00:05:20.987 --> 00:05:23.364
You know? Doing what teenage boys do.

99
00:05:23.448 --> 00:05:24.532
Yeah.

100
00:05:24.949 --> 00:05:26.868
I mean. that's what I was doing
at that age.

101
00:05:26.951 --> 00:05:28.119
Uh-huh.

102
00:05:30.872 --> 00:05:32.999
Listen. I'd still appreciate it
if you all would...

103
00:05:33.082 --> 00:05:34.417
Ma'am. we will.

104
00:05:34.500 --> 00:05:36.753
But you said that before.
and you're leaving.

105
00:05:37.170 --> 00:05:39.922
And I would really like to know
what is going on.

106
00:05:40.006 --> 00:05:42.759
Look. I told you. as soon as
the AM liaison officer gets here...

107
00:05:42.842 --> 00:05:43.843
- No. I mean now.
- Sorry?

108
00:05:43.926 --> 00:05:44.927
I want to know now.

109
00:05:45.011 --> 00:05:48.556
Well. I will be happy to walk you back out
to reception.

110
00:05:48.639 --> 00:05:52.018
- You could check again to see...
- I was just at reception for half an hour.

111
00:05:52.101 --> 00:05:54.204
- There's not much more I can...
- And the lady there.

112
00:05:54.228 --> 00:05:56.814
- she was no help at all.
- I... I understand.

113
00:05:56.898 --> 00:05:58.858
Look. she sent me to you.
This can't be that hard.

114
00:05:58.941 --> 00:06:01.587
- I'm very sorry. ma'am. I...
- Either he's in the system or he isn't.

115
00:06:01.611 --> 00:06:03.371
Ma'am. no disrespect.
but we have a protocol.

116
00:06:03.446 --> 00:06:06.240
Listen. I may seem paranoid.
but he's not home.

117
00:06:07.408 --> 00:06:11.037
His car is showing up on your radar.

118
00:06:11.120 --> 00:06:12.163
- Humor me.
- Ma'am.

119
00:06:12.246 --> 00:06:14.248
as soon
as the AM liaison officer gets here.

120
00:06:14.332 --> 00:06:15.708
Officer. please.

121
00:06:15.792 --> 00:06:18.771
- I don't know what you expect me to do.
- Well. don't you all have computers?

122
00:06:18.795 --> 00:06:21.464
I don't know. a database with names
and DOBs you can...

123
00:06:21.547 --> 00:06:24.884
Yes. but I am not authorized
to just go running down the rabbit hole.

124
00:06:24.967 --> 00:06:26.969
- What if somebody walks in. and they...?
- Please.

125
00:06:28.137 --> 00:06:29.305
[sighs]

126
00:06:35.103 --> 00:06:36.396
- Fine.
- [weeping]

127
00:06:37.021 --> 00:06:37.897
[softly] Thank you.

128
00:06:37.980 --> 00:06:39.857
But I'm gonna need
some additional information.

129
00:06:39.941 --> 00:06:40.817
- Sure.
- All right.

130
00:06:40.900 --> 00:06:42.985
Just let me... Let me get something.

131
00:06:44.654 --> 00:06:46.239
- [lock screen clicks]
- [thuds]

132
00:06:46.864 --> 00:06:49.033
[phone keyboard clicking]

133
00:06:52.537 --> 00:06:53.538
Hmm.

134
00:06:53.621 --> 00:06:54.914
[outbound text swooshes]

135
00:07:03.631 --> 00:07:04.549
First name again?

136
00:07:04.632 --> 00:07:06.342
Jamal. J-A-M-A-L.

137
00:07:06.717 --> 00:07:07.717
Last name. Connor.

138
00:07:07.760 --> 00:07:08.760
Yes. [chuckles]

139
00:07:09.846 --> 00:07:11.305
- Is that E-R?
- No. O-R.

140
00:07:11.389 --> 00:07:12.640
C-O-N-N-O-R.

141
00:07:12.723 --> 00:07:13.641
DOB?

142
00:07:13.724 --> 00:07:15.101
5/1/2001.

143
00:07:15.184 --> 00:07:16.184
Any priors?

144
00:07:17.061 --> 00:07:18.061
Sorry?

145
00:07:18.271 --> 00:07:20.648
Priors.
Has he ever been arrested before?

146
00:07:21.691 --> 00:07:22.984
Oh. No. [chuckles]

147
00:07:23.067 --> 00:07:23.985
- Are you sure?
- Yes.

148
00:07:24.068 --> 00:07:26.070
- Even juvie.
- Juvie?

149
00:07:26.446 --> 00:07:28.531
- Does he have a <i>juvenile</i> record?
- No.

150
00:07:28.614 --> 00:07:30.032
- Nothing?
- Nothing.

151
00:07:31.659 --> 00:07:34.537
Not even a trespassing
or resisting without. petty theft?

152
00:07:34.620 --> 00:07:37.874
He's never so much as torn the tag
off a new mattress. okay?

153
00:07:37.957 --> 00:07:39.375
- Excuse me?
- Nothing.

154
00:07:39.459 --> 00:07:41.377
No... No arrest record at all.

155
00:07:42.211 --> 00:07:44.922
Hmm. Uh. does he go by any other names?

156
00:07:45.256 --> 00:07:46.340
Like a nickname?

157
00:07:46.424 --> 00:07:47.884
I mean. his father calls him J.

158
00:07:47.967 --> 00:07:49.427
No. Uh. AKAs?

159
00:07:51.012 --> 00:07:52.638
- I'm sorry?
- AKAs.

160
00:07:52.930 --> 00:07:55.808
You know. "also known as."
Like. street names.

161
00:07:55.892 --> 00:07:57.101
Street names?

162
00:07:57.185 --> 00:08:00.855
Yeah. Well. if he was taken into custody
under a different alias. right?

163
00:08:00.938 --> 00:08:03.274
He gave a different...
Well. different from some other time

164
00:08:03.357 --> 00:08:05.902
- is all I'm saying.
- I just told you he's never been arrested.

165
00:08:05.985 --> 00:08:08.112
But just in case
he might have been printed for.

166
00:08:08.196 --> 00:08:11.574
I don't know. whatever.
Or had a warning issued. or...

167
00:08:12.158 --> 00:08:13.493
- A street name?
- Right.

168
00:08:14.619 --> 00:08:16.996
- Like Peanut? Or Black?
- Exactly.

169
00:08:17.079 --> 00:08:18.080
Or Pookie.

170
00:08:19.081 --> 00:08:20.081
Yes. ma'am.

171
00:08:22.418 --> 00:08:24.212
Well. there's June Bug.

172
00:08:24.545 --> 00:08:25.880
- June Bug.
- Yup.

173
00:08:25.963 --> 00:08:28.007
- That's his street name?
- Jesus Christ.

174
00:08:28.090 --> 00:08:29.091
- [officer] Is it?
- No.

175
00:08:30.593 --> 00:08:32.428
It's not an alias. It's not a street name.

176
00:08:32.512 --> 00:08:33.346
You sure?

177
00:08:33.429 --> 00:08:35.431
It's what I used to call him
when he was little.

178
00:08:36.849 --> 00:08:39.077
It's what I call him now
when I want to knock the cool out of him

179
00:08:39.101 --> 00:08:41.261
in front of his friends.
He doesn't have a street name.

180
00:08:42.355 --> 00:08:45.733
Can you please just run all this
through your computer...

181
00:08:45.816 --> 00:08:48.653
- Ma'am! I am going to.
- ...and find out what is going on?

182
00:08:48.736 --> 00:08:51.781
I just need to make sure that we have
all the correct information here.

183
00:08:51.864 --> 00:08:53.824
so we aren't just spinning our wheels.

184
00:08:53.908 --> 00:08:55.910
[thunder rumbling]

185
00:08:58.579 --> 00:08:59.579
Fine.

186
00:09:04.001 --> 00:09:05.001
Height?

187
00:09:05.962 --> 00:09:06.962
Six-two.

188
00:09:07.630 --> 00:09:09.733
Maybe a little taller
since last time we measured him.

189
00:09:09.757 --> 00:09:11.842
- He really shot up this year...
- Uh-huh. Weight?

190
00:09:16.222 --> 00:09:20.351
Uh. 180... 185. thereabouts.

191
00:09:27.233 --> 00:09:28.234
Glasses.

192
00:09:28.734 --> 00:09:29.734
Hmm.

193
00:09:30.653 --> 00:09:31.654
Cornrows.

194
00:09:34.240 --> 00:09:35.491
Light green eyes.

195
00:09:39.036 --> 00:09:40.036
[officer] Okay. good.

196
00:09:40.079 --> 00:09:43.708
Uh. do you remember what he was wearing
when he left last night?

197
00:09:45.251 --> 00:09:47.670
I-I don't know.
Probably jeans and a T-shirt.

198
00:09:48.754 --> 00:09:51.757
All right. Does he have
any distinguishing. you know...

199
00:09:54.427 --> 00:09:55.595
Like a birthmark?

200
00:09:55.678 --> 00:09:59.682
Yeah. Scars. tattoos. gold teeth.
That kind of stuff.

201
00:10:00.266 --> 00:10:02.893
No. No tattoos. No golds.

202
00:10:04.645 --> 00:10:07.481
His only scar is on his stomach.
right here.

203
00:10:07.565 --> 00:10:09.108
Great. And that's from?

204
00:10:09.191 --> 00:10:11.068
- The scar?
- Yeah. where did he get it?

205
00:10:11.777 --> 00:10:13.529
You mean. how did he get it?

206
00:10:13.613 --> 00:10:15.323
Well. both. I guess. yeah.

207
00:10:15.406 --> 00:10:16.883
- Does this matter?
- [officer] Ma'am...

208
00:10:16.907 --> 00:10:18.635
- It's not from a gang fight.
- [officer] Okay.

209
00:10:18.659 --> 00:10:19.869
- Lady. listen...
- Officer.

210
00:10:19.952 --> 00:10:23.539
Respectfully. are there
that many 6'2" black boys

211
00:10:23.623 --> 00:10:25.249
involved in incidents tonight.

212
00:10:25.333 --> 00:10:26.959
you need to know
if they might just have

213
00:10:27.043 --> 00:10:28.127
scars on their tummies?

214
00:10:28.210 --> 00:10:30.254
Not unless you want to find him. I mean...

215
00:10:30.338 --> 00:10:33.424
Okay. Jamal's sign is Taurus
with Virgo rising.

216
00:10:33.507 --> 00:10:35.885
He's bashful. looks away when he smiles.

217
00:10:35.968 --> 00:10:38.155
- Really. I am just looking for...
- He plays the guitar.

218
00:10:38.179 --> 00:10:39.859
- Especially likes blues and rock.
- Ma'am.

219
00:10:39.930 --> 00:10:41.617
- Old '70s and '80s bands.
- [officer] Ma'am...

220
00:10:41.641 --> 00:10:43.517
I tried to turn him on to Funkadelic

221
00:10:43.601 --> 00:10:45.061
- and DeBarge...
- Ma'am. I...

222
00:10:45.144 --> 00:10:46.747
...but he's strictly
mainstream classic stuff.

223
00:10:46.771 --> 00:10:48.707
- Clapton. Van Halen.
- [officer. irritably] Okay.

224
00:10:48.731 --> 00:10:50.667
He throws a mean breaking ball.
whatever that means.

225
00:10:50.691 --> 00:10:52.044
- All right. Listen...
- He's vegetarian.

226
00:10:52.068 --> 00:10:54.612
hates fried chicken.
and he's afraid of clowns.

227
00:10:54.695 --> 00:10:56.280
- Ma'am...
- He walks like a jock.

228
00:10:56.364 --> 00:10:59.033
but he can recite
almost any Emily Dickinson poem.

229
00:10:59.116 --> 00:11:00.951
- Okay.
- And he still gets a tear in his eye

230
00:11:01.035 --> 00:11:03.037
whenever he hears
"Puff the Magic Dragon."

231
00:11:04.664 --> 00:11:06.666
[thunder rumbling]

232
00:11:06.749 --> 00:11:07.958
[woman sighs]

233
00:11:08.709 --> 00:11:09.709
Sorry.

234
00:11:20.763 --> 00:11:22.598
I-I love Emily Dickinson.

235
00:11:24.767 --> 00:11:28.604
"It is a far. far better thing I do
than I've ever done.

236
00:11:29.480 --> 00:11:32.191
- It is a far. far better..."
- That's Charles Dickens.

237
00:11:33.442 --> 00:11:35.945
Mmm... I don't think so.

238
00:11:38.155 --> 00:11:40.783
Anyway. uh. let me see
what I can find out. okay?

239
00:11:40.866 --> 00:11:44.704
Oh. hey. was he angry or upset
about anything last night?

240
00:11:45.079 --> 00:11:46.079
Why?

241
00:11:46.539 --> 00:11:49.417
Well. just in case he had a reason to.
you know. run off

242
00:11:49.500 --> 00:11:51.460
and chill for a while.

243
00:11:52.503 --> 00:11:53.546
No.

244
00:11:54.296 --> 00:11:56.298
- [thunder crashes]
- Okay. Cool.

245
00:11:56.382 --> 00:11:59.135
