- [Ellis-Connor] It's okay.

494
00:24:56.995 --> 00:24:58.473
- Of course.
- God damn it. I got him the car.

495
00:24:58.497 --> 00:25:00.141
- You know I knew that.
- Hey. I said it's okay.

496
00:25:00.165 --> 00:25:02.560
It's four o'clock in the morning.
I haven't had a cup of coffee.

497
00:25:02.584 --> 00:25:03.418
- I understand.
- Look...

498
00:25:03.502 --> 00:25:05.253
Lieutenant Stokes
should be here very soon.

499
00:25:05.337 --> 00:25:08.657
I wanna know what's going on with my son.
you've been in contact with the detective.

500
00:25:08.715 --> 00:25:09.715
I'd like to have a word.

501
00:25:09.758 --> 00:25:10.985
- [Larkin] No. sir.
- Excuse me?

502
00:25:11.009 --> 00:25:13.845
I have not been in contact
with the GIU detective.

503
00:25:13.929 --> 00:25:15.769
[Scott] Two seconds ago.
you just said you had.

504
00:25:15.805 --> 00:25:18.016
No. sir. That is not correct.
I got somebody in GIU

505
00:25:18.099 --> 00:25:21.895
to... to read me a bit of information.
secondhand. off the daily log sheet.

506
00:25:21.978 --> 00:25:22.979
- That is all.
- Uh-huh.

507
00:25:23.063 --> 00:25:25.333
I've not been able to speak with anybody
about the case yet.

508
00:25:25.357 --> 00:25:29.903
There's a protocol that we have to follow.
and it involves the AM liaison officer.

509
00:25:29.986 --> 00:25:32.989
- And you don't know when he'll be here?
- Very soon. I hope.

510
00:25:36.076 --> 00:25:38.828
But if you'd rather not wait here.
that's fine.

511
00:25:38.912 --> 00:25:42.016
Uh. you can leave me your cell number.
I'd be happy to call you when he arrives.

512
00:25:42.040 --> 00:25:43.750
There's a Denny's on the corner.

513
00:25:43.833 --> 00:25:46.378
- Yeah. it's a very short walk.
- Thank you. We'll wait.

514
00:25:47.963 --> 00:25:48.963
Sure.

515
00:25:49.631 --> 00:25:51.258
Can I... Can I get you anything?

516
00:25:51.341 --> 00:25:52.259
- Coffee?
- I'm fine.

517
00:25:52.342 --> 00:25:53.426
Coffee would be great.

518
00:25:53.510 --> 00:25:55.554
- [Larkin] Cream? Sugar?
- No. I like it black.

519
00:25:55.637 --> 00:25:56.637
Well...

520
00:26:01.309 --> 00:26:03.353
[Larkin] Listen. I'm sure
that this is no big deal.

521
00:26:03.436 --> 00:26:06.356
I just started working here.
but they tell me this happens every night.

522
00:26:06.439 --> 00:26:07.274
[scoffs]

523
00:26:07.357 --> 00:26:10.110
We have a skeleton crew in admin
on the late shift.

524
00:26:10.193 --> 00:26:13.196
It can take forever for information
to filter down. so...

525
00:26:13.280 --> 00:26:15.490
Well. I apologize if I was. you know...

526
00:26:15.574 --> 00:26:16.616
[Larkin] No. not at all.

527
00:26:16.700 --> 00:26:19.578
And. listen. I'm really sorry
about when you came in and I...

528
00:26:19.661 --> 00:26:21.121
- Yeah.
- Sorry about what?

529
00:26:21.204 --> 00:26:22.204
Nothing.

530
00:26:29.170 --> 00:26:30.171
- FBI. huh?
- Yeah.

531
00:26:30.255 --> 00:26:31.524
- That's awesome.
- [Scott] Thanks.

532
00:26:31.548 --> 00:26:32.608
[Larkin] It's my dream job.

533
00:26:32.632 --> 00:26:34.259
- Is it?
- Mm-hmm. Behavioral analysis.

534
00:26:34.342 --> 00:26:35.927
- Really?
- Yeah. I applied.

535
00:26:36.011 --> 00:26:38.054
but they told me
I needed investigative experience.

536
00:26:38.138 --> 00:26:39.431
which is why I joined the force.

537
00:26:39.514 --> 00:26:42.017
[Scott] Well. I hope you kicked ass
in differential equations

538
00:26:42.100 --> 00:26:43.452
- or whatever...
- [chuckling] Yeah.

539
00:26:43.476 --> 00:26:46.187
BS in Forensics at Jacksonville State.
Go. Gamecocks!

540
00:26:46.271 --> 00:26:48.191
Good. 'Cause those guys
in the Ted Bundy Brigade.

541
00:26:48.231 --> 00:26:49.107
they're smart as hell.

542
00:26:49.190 --> 00:26:51.460
[Larkin chuckling] The Ted Bundy Brigade.
that is awesome.

543
00:26:51.484 --> 00:26:53.111
Yeah. They don't like to be called that.

544
00:26:53.194 --> 00:26:55.590
It's what the rest of us call 'em
when we wanna piss 'em off.

545
00:26:55.614 --> 00:26:56.448
Right.

546
00:26:56.531 --> 00:26:59.010
I'd be happy to put a good word in for you
when the time comes.

547
00:26:59.034 --> 00:27:00.344
- [Larkin] Really?
- Give me a call.

548
00:27:00.368 --> 00:27:01.494
That would be so awesome.

549
00:27:01.578 --> 00:27:02.888
- Thank you so much.
- [Scott] You bet.

550
00:27:02.912 --> 00:27:04.623
So. the Lexus.

551
00:27:04.706 --> 00:27:05.999
It's registered to me.

552
00:27:06.374 --> 00:27:07.292
- The...
- The car.

553
00:27:07.375 --> 00:27:09.294
my son's car. is registered in my name.

554
00:27:09.377 --> 00:27:10.629
Scott Alan Connor.

555
00:27:10.712 --> 00:27:12.881
- It was a birthday gift.
- [Larkin] Oh. nice.

556
00:27:12.964 --> 00:27:15.342
Yeah. Well. pre-owned.
Still a little indulgent. I guess...

557
00:27:15.425 --> 00:27:16.425
Oh. yeah. Whatever.

558
00:27:16.468 --> 00:27:17.802
He worked very hard.

559
00:27:17.886 --> 00:27:19.572
- Bit of a reach for us. but...
- We thought he'd earned it.

560
00:27:19.596 --> 00:27:21.890
[Scott] Anyway. we kept it in my name
for the insurance.

561
00:27:21.973 --> 00:27:24.100
But I can tell all that
to the GIU guy myself

562
00:27:24.184 --> 00:27:26.019
when you bring me down there
to talk to him.

563
00:27:26.102 --> 00:27:28.021
Right. So. coffee...

564
00:27:28.897 --> 00:27:29.897
No cream. no sugar.

565
00:27:29.939 --> 00:27:30.939
I'm on it.

566
00:27:36.738 --> 00:27:38.073
[Scott sighs]

567
00:27:40.617 --> 00:27:41.617
What?

568
00:27:42.327 --> 00:27:43.453
- What?
- Nothing.

569
00:27:43.536 --> 00:27:45.246
No. not nothing. What?

570
00:27:45.330 --> 00:27:47.666
Why don't you just offer
to cut and blow out his hair.

571
00:27:47.749 --> 00:27:49.626
give him a hand massage. for God's sake?

572
00:27:49.709 --> 00:27:50.709
- Kendra.
- I mean...

573
00:27:50.752 --> 00:27:52.392
- I'm just trying to be civil.
- Whatever.

574
00:27:52.420 --> 00:27:53.898
- Acting all crazy...
- Who's acting crazy?

575
00:27:53.922 --> 00:27:55.340
...isn't gonna help the situation.

576
00:27:56.007 --> 00:27:57.425
They have our son.

577
00:27:58.051 --> 00:28:00.261
We wanna know where he is.
They can tell us.

578
00:28:00.345 --> 00:28:01.346
This ain't complicated.

579
00:28:01.429 --> 00:28:02.681
This is a bureaucracy.

580
00:28:02.764 --> 00:28:05.034
I think you're assuming the worst.
when the truth be told.

581
00:28:05.058 --> 00:28:06.827
the current situation
is probably a whole nother thing.

582
00:28:06.851 --> 00:28:08.411
- Oh...
- Look. I work at a bureaucracy.

583
00:28:08.436 --> 00:28:10.122
I'm telling you.
you're not gonna get anywhere

584
00:28:10.146 --> 00:28:11.940
chewing out some low-level yes-man.

585
00:28:12.023 --> 00:28:13.817
I've been here for almost an hour.

586
00:28:13.900 --> 00:28:15.360
- Look. alls I'm saying...
- "All."

587
00:28:15.443 --> 00:28:16.443
All?

588
00:28:16.528 --> 00:28:17.904
<i>"All </i>you're saying."

589
00:28:17.987 --> 00:28:20.740
"All" is not plural.
It's not a possessive.

590
00:28:20.824 --> 00:28:23.410
There's no such word as "alls."
Just "all."

591
00:28:24.786 --> 00:28:25.870
Seriously?

592
00:28:26.496 --> 00:28:28.206
Jamal doesn't "ax a question."

593
00:28:28.289 --> 00:28:29.666
He doesn't speak Ebonics.

594
00:28:29.749 --> 00:28:32.627
- You don't get to speak white trash.
- Oh. Christ. Kendra...

595
00:28:32.711 --> 00:28:33.711
"Alls I'm saying."

596
00:28:33.753 --> 00:28:34.879
"A whole nother."

597
00:28:34.963 --> 00:28:36.047
Just purge that shit.

598
00:28:36.131 --> 00:28:37.525
- I'm sorry. "A whole nother"?
- Yeah.

599
00:28:37.549 --> 00:28:39.968
"The current situation is probably
a whole nother thing."

600
00:28:40.051 --> 00:28:41.720
Sweet sweating Jesus. Kendra.

601
00:28:41.803 --> 00:28:43.364
- The word is "another." One word.
- Okay.

602
00:28:43.388 --> 00:28:45.557
Don't go shoving the word "whole"
in the middle of it.

603
00:28:45.640 --> 00:28:47.684
Can we not just go off in the weeds
on some...

604
00:28:47.767 --> 00:28:49.352
This isn't "off in the weeds."

605
00:28:50.395 --> 00:28:53.732
You know how I killed myself to make sure
Jamal speaks proper English.

606
00:28:53.815 --> 00:28:55.900
- Yeah. believe me. I know. Yeah.
- Okay? Good.

607
00:28:57.736 --> 00:28:59.738
[thunder rumbling]

608
00:29:05.452 --> 00:29:07.454
I mean. you just said "ain't"
two seconds ago.

609
00:29:07.537 --> 00:29:09.581
but I <i>ain't</i> allowed to.
That makes perfect sense.

610
00:29:09.706 --> 00:29:11.374
I said "ain't" for emphasis.

611
00:29:11.458 --> 00:29:13.168
- You just speak bad English.
- Jesus.

612
00:29:13.251 --> 00:29:15.170
It's like every little thing
with you lately.

613
00:29:15.253 --> 00:29:17.088
No. this isn't every <i>little</i> thing.

614
00:29:18.339 --> 00:29:22.051
As hard as I worked to make him fit in.

615
00:29:22.135 --> 00:29:25.138
it's a slap in my face
when you cavalierly lapse

616
00:29:25.221 --> 00:29:26.681
into "Okie from Muskogee."

617
00:29:27.182 --> 00:29:28.183
Can we just...

618
00:29:28.683 --> 00:29:30.911
Let's see if we can get our arms
around the here and now.

619
00:29:30.935 --> 00:29:32.854
Find out where J's at and not. you know.

620
00:29:32.937 --> 00:29:34.617
rehash the last five years
of our marriage.

621
00:29:34.689 --> 00:29:35.958
- Would that be okay?
- [Kendra] Sure.

622
00:29:35.982 --> 00:29:36.982
Good.

623
00:29:38.860 --> 00:29:40.236
[lock screen clicks]

624
00:29:40.320 --> 00:29:42.739
And I've never forced you
to make him fit in.

625
00:29:42.822 --> 00:29:44.657
- Whatever.
- Hey. I let you name him Jamal.

626
00:29:44.741 --> 00:29:46.284
- Didn't I?
- "Let me"?

627
00:29:46.743 --> 00:29:48.036
- Here we go again.
- Right?

628
00:29:48.119 --> 00:29:49.370
Baby. I'm sorry.

629
00:29:49.454 --> 00:29:52.248
I love your Irish people and all.

630
00:29:52.332 --> 00:29:54.727
but I simply wasn't gonna go through life
with a son named...

631
00:29:54.751 --> 00:29:57.003
What was it you were putting on the table
at the time?

632
00:29:57.378 --> 00:29:58.546
Seamus.

633
00:29:58.630 --> 00:30:01.132
- [chuckling] Hell. no.
- [Scott chuckling]

634
00:30:01.549 --> 00:30:04.469
I'd have gone with something else.
Liam. Aidan...

635
00:30:04.552 --> 00:30:05.595
Lord.

636
00:30:06.012 --> 00:30:08.014
[laughing]

637
00:30:08.932 --> 00:30:11.226
I needed to commemorate my brother.

638
00:30:14.938 --> 00:30:16.648
I thought you understood that.

639
00:30:17.357 --> 00:30:18.191
I did.

640
00:30:18.274 --> 00:30:19.317
[scoffs]

641
00:30:19.567 --> 00:30:20.567
You know...

642
00:30:20.902 --> 00:30:23.863
you may not remember.
but in Arabic. Jamal means beauty.

643
00:30:23.947 --> 00:30:25.824
Means beauty. Yes. how could I forget?

644
00:30:27.242 --> 00:30:29.244
"Hey. Beauty.
You wanna toss a football around?"

645
00:30:29.327 --> 00:30:31.246
- [scoffs]
- I can't wait 'til he's 21

646
00:30:31.329 --> 00:30:33.540
so me and the guys can head on over
to the tavern

647
00:30:33.623 --> 00:30:35.667
and hoist a glass of whiskey
with ol' Beauty.

648
00:30:35.750 --> 00:30:37.144
- My. oh. my.
- Maybe he'll bring his friends

649
00:30:37.168 --> 00:30:39.712
Chastity and Mother's Milk
along as designated drivers.

650
00:30:39.796 --> 00:30:41.756
Is your sense of masculinity
really that delicate?

651
00:30:41.840 --> 00:30:44.342
- [outbound text swoosh]
- Of course not. Kenny. Come on.

652
00:30:44.843 --> 00:30:46.483
It's just a hell of a fun button to push.

653
00:30:46.511 --> 00:30:49.305
His name is fine. all right?

654
00:30:52.267 --> 00:30:54.227
You can't even say it half the time.

655
00:30:55.228 --> 00:30:57.188
It's always "J" this. "J" that.

656
00:30:57.272 --> 00:31:00.608
Oh. come on. I got a nickname for my son.
That's just a male bonding thing.

657
00:31:00.692 --> 00:31:01.901
Just man up and say it.

658
00:31:01.985 --> 00:31:03.695
You've always hated his name...

659
00:31:03.987 --> 00:31:05.405
because it's too black.

660
00:31:05.905 --> 00:31:07.156
You're the one who just said

661
00:31:07.240 --> 00:31:10.243
- Seamus was too Irish.
- You think his name's a handicap.

662
00:31:10.326 --> 00:31:12.620
Well. you know what? On a scale from...

663
00:31:13.121 --> 00:31:16.583
Eric Holder to. you know. Darnell Jackson.

664
00:31:17.417 --> 00:31:19.586
Jamal is brushing
right up against Darnell.

665
00:31:21.504 --> 00:31:25.383
It must be terrible feeling so alienated
from your own flesh and blood.

666
00:31:26.259 --> 00:31:29.387
Hey. I'd challenge hell's furies
for that kid. and you know that.

667
00:31:31.180 --> 00:31:32.181
My only son.

668
00:31:36.936 --> 00:31:40.106
- Should we try calling him again?
- I've already tried about 15 times.

669
00:31:40.189 --> 00:31:41.608
I just keep getting his voicemail.

670
00:31:41.691 --> 00:31:44.611
Yeah. me too.
"Hey. this is Jamal. Have a <i>blessed</i> day."

671
00:31:44.694 --> 00:31:46.446
When did that bullshit start?

672
00:31:46.654 --> 00:31:48.698
He's been going
with me and Mama to church.

673
00:31:50.408 --> 00:31:51.743
Thank you. by the way.

674
00:31:51.826 --> 00:31:53.870
- [Scott] For what?
- For taking her to dialysis.

675
00:31:53.953 --> 00:31:55.830
- [Scott] Oh. please.
- No. it's a huge help.

676
00:31:55.914 --> 00:31:57.594
Bobby's like my own mother. you know that.

677
00:31:57.624 --> 00:31:59.351
- [Kendra] I know.
- She is a tough old broad.

678
00:31:59.375 --> 00:32:02.253
She thinks the sun rises and sets on you.

679
00:32:05.924 --> 00:32:07.926
She blames me for all of this.

680
00:32:08.635 --> 00:32:09.635
[scoffs]

681
00:32:15.391 --> 00:32:16.684
[sighs]

682
00:32:17.268 --> 00:32:18.353
You look good.

683
00:32:18.436 --> 00:32:20.063
- Oh. Jesus.
- [Scott] Well. you do.

684
00:32:20.146 --> 00:32:21.397
Please don't go there.

685
00:32:21.481 --> 00:32:23.417
We haven't really
seen each other since... you know.

686
00:32:23.441 --> 00:32:25.001
- Oh. I know.
- Oh. can't I just notice?

687
00:32:25.068 --> 00:32:26.152
What did you expect. Scott?

688
00:32:26.235 --> 00:32:28.488
Four months without you.
and I'd completely fall apart?

689
00:32:28.571 --> 00:32:29.822
Is that what you were hoping?

690
00:32:29.906 --> 00:32:32.367
- Christ. Forget I said anything.
- Yes! Let's just forget it.

691
00:32:32.450 --> 00:32:35.286
Let's just find our son and go back
to our respective corners. okay?

692
00:32:35.370 --> 00:32:36.704
- [Scott] Fine.
- [phone chimes]

693
00:32:39.791 --> 00:32:40.791
Is it Jamal?

694
00:32:42.210 --> 00:32:43.211
No.

695
00:32:43.795 --> 00:32:45.713
So. where was he last night?

696
00:32:45.797 --> 00:32:47.298
- I assume he went out.
- Yeah.

697
00:32:47.382 --> 00:32:48.549
- With who?
- I don't know.

698
00:32:48.633 --> 00:32:49.467
You don't know?

699
00:32:49.550 --> 00:32:52.011
- Why should I know?
- Jesus Christ. Kendra.

700
00:32:52.095 --> 00:32:54.015
I don't grill him every time
he leaves the house.

701
00:32:54.055 --> 00:32:55.682
He's a grown man. I trust his judgment.

702
00:32:55.765 --> 00:32:57.976
You're the one who insisted
that J live with you.

703
00:32:58.059 --> 00:32:59.370
- [chuckles]
- Which I was okay with.

704
00:32:59.394 --> 00:33:01.288
But you took on an obligation
to be responsible...

705
00:33:01.312 --> 00:33:03.940
I thought we weren't going to rehash
our entire relationship?

706
00:33:04.023 --> 00:33:05.274
- Okay. Fine.
- [Kendra] Fine.

707
00:33:05.358 --> 00:33:06.877
It's just. I hate to keep harping on it.

708
00:33:06.901 --> 00:33:09.195
but this kid's going to West Point
in. like. a month.

709
00:33:09.278 --> 00:33:11.990
- It is just not acceptable that he...
- Here we go.

710
00:33:12.073 --> 00:33:13.241
It's not. Kenny.

711
00:33:15.368 --> 00:33:18.329
Last few times he stayed at my place.
he looked like a goddamned gangster.

712
00:33:18.413 --> 00:33:19.706
A gangster?

713
00:33:19.789 --> 00:33:21.541
Yeah. A "gangsta." There. I said it.

714
00:33:21.624 --> 00:33:24.252
Why? Because he's not wearing
Brooks Brothers?

715
00:33:24.335 --> 00:33:26.587
Oh. the baggy pants. the cornrows.

716
00:33:26.671 --> 00:33:30.341
that stupid loping.
surly walk he suddenly developed.

717
00:33:30.425 --> 00:33:32.218
He's a teenage boy. okay?

718
00:33:32.301 --> 00:33:35.280
- A second ago he was a grown man.
- He's just trying to figure out who he is.

719
00:33:35.304 --> 00:33:38.099
- Oh. he's trying to figure out who he is?
- Explore his own identity.

720
00:33:38.182 --> 00:33:39.726
Christ almighty. Today it's cornrows.

721
00:33:39.809 --> 00:33:42.395
tomorrow he'll be out helping OJ
find the real killer.

722
00:33:42.478 --> 00:33:45.356
Okay. See that right there?
Comments like that...

723
00:33:46.107 --> 00:33:49.152
You just don't get it.
His world is not your world. Scott.

724
00:33:49.235 --> 00:33:51.112
Oh. yes. it is. It most certainly is.

725
00:33:51.195 --> 00:33:53.948
Look. I completely appreciate
how you had to grow up.

726
00:33:54.032 --> 00:33:56.617
Okay? The hard streets of Liberty City.

727
00:33:56.701 --> 00:33:58.953
Interstate cutting through. Redlining.
All of that.

728
00:33:59.037 --> 00:34:00.997
I admire it. I always have.

729
00:34:02.081 --> 00:34:03.583
It's one of the many reasons I...

730
00:34:06.878 --> 00:34:07.878
You what?

731
00:34:12.300 --> 00:34:14.635
- You what?
- His world is not that world.

732
00:34:14.719 --> 00:34:16.804
His world is definitely my world.

733
00:34:16.888 --> 00:34:18.890
We worked hard to make it my world.

734
00:34:18.973 --> 00:34:21.100
We spent almost
a quarter of a million dollars

735
00:34:21.184 --> 00:34:23.495
putting that kid
through the best prep schools in the city.

736
00:34:23.519 --> 00:34:25.646
He grew up in Coral Gables.
for Christ's sake.

737
00:34:25.730 --> 00:34:27.106
He's had every possible advantage.

738
00:34:27.190 --> 00:34:29.484
I simply will not accept him
regressing into...

739
00:34:29.567 --> 00:34:31.027
Into what?

740
00:34:32.487 --> 00:34:33.696
Just say it. Scott.

741
00:34:33.780 --> 00:34:36.866
That young man has no excuse
for getting himself into this situation.

742
00:34:36.949 --> 00:34:38.326
What situation?

743
00:34:38.743 --> 00:34:40.411
We don't even know what happened yet.

744
00:34:40.495 --> 00:34:42.705
Something happened.
I can take a pretty good guess what.

745
00:34:42.789 --> 00:34:46.417
Why are you automatically gonna blame him
before you even know anything?

746
00:34:46.501 --> 00:34:48.062
You know he's driving around
with two black kids?

747
00:34:48.086 --> 00:34:48.920
Oh. God forbid.

748
00:34:49.003 --> 00:34:50.463
Oh. please don't. Don't do that.

749
00:34:50.588 --> 00:34:51.422
Are you kidding me?

750
00:34:51.506 --> 00:34:54.777
Look. Kenny. it's just you and me in here.
so you can quit with the performance art.

751
00:34:54.801 --> 00:34:56.094
- Seriously?
- Kendra. come on.

752
00:34:56.177 --> 00:34:58.537
He was out with two other black kids.
that's the issue here?

753
00:34:58.596 --> 00:34:59.847
I mean what if...

754
00:35:03.518 --> 00:35:05.186
How do you know who he was with?

755
00:35:08.064 --> 00:35:09.064
This guy.

756
00:35:10.358 --> 00:35:11.567
- This cop?
- Yeah.

757
00:35:11.651 --> 00:35:13.861
- Well... when?
- When I walked in.

758
00:35:18.157 --> 00:35:21.327
[scoffs] So the whole hour I'm here.
he doesn't know a thing.

759
00:35:21.410 --> 00:35:24.580
The minute you walk in the door.
he's full of answers.

760
00:35:24.664 --> 00:35:26.391
I wouldn't necessarily say
"full of answers."

761
00:35:26.415 --> 00:35:28.268
But he told you Jamal was in a car
with two kids?

762
00:35:28.292 --> 00:35:29.812
- They were stopped.
- Two other black kids.

763
00:35:29.836 --> 00:35:31.796
- Yeah.
- Well. he never told <i>me</i> any of that.

764
00:35:31.879 --> 00:35:33.089
I wonder why that might be.

765
00:35:33.172 --> 00:35:36.134
Right now. I don't really care.
I just wanna know who they are.

766
00:35:36.217 --> 00:35:37.802
Didn't your new buddy there tell you?

767
00:35:37.885 --> 00:35:38.885
No.

768
00:35:39.720 --> 00:35:41.681
And I think you'll agree this demonstrates

769
00:35:41.764 --> 00:35:43.404
- some pretty questionable judgment.
- No.

770
00:35:43.432 --> 00:35:44.767
- Not necessarily.
- Really?

771
00:35:44.851 --> 00:35:47.311
He's got a right to be in a car
with his friends

772
00:35:47.395 --> 00:35:49.438
without getting dragged downtown
at 3:00 a.m.

773
00:35:49.522 --> 00:35:51.125
No one's saying
he doesn't have a right...

774
00:35:51.149 --> 00:35:52.909
Even if he's in a car
with his <i>black </i>friends!

775
00:35:52.942 --> 00:35:54.622
- What black friends?
- Oh. Scott. come on.

776
00:35:54.652 --> 00:35:55.652
What are you...

777
00:35:56.195 --> 00:35:57.572
Can't you see what you're saying?

778
00:35:57.655 --> 00:35:59.615
This is exactly what I'm saying.
Listen to me.

779
00:35:59.699 --> 00:36:00.783
What black friends?

780
00:36:00.867 --> 00:36:02.034
Was he with Jeffrey?

781
00:36:03.035 --> 00:36:06.080
Was he out with Nate or Manny?
Kids that we know and trust?

782
00:36:06.164 --> 00:36:08.433
- Because that'd be one thing.
- I told you. I don't know.

783
00:36:08.457 --> 00:36:10.084
No. And he certainly wasn't out with Al.

784
00:36:10.168 --> 00:36:12.170
No. Al's in Europe with his family
on vacation.

785
00:36:12.253 --> 00:36:15.047
Yeah. And Al is the only black kid
he hangs out with.

786
00:36:15.131 --> 00:36:18.217
- which is exactly my point.
- Funny. That's <i>exactly</i> my point.

787
00:36:18.301 --> 00:36:21.179
- Oh. look. Kendra. I...
- You think our bougie son

788
00:36:21.262 --> 00:36:23.598
has no right to associate
with other black kids

789
00:36:23.681 --> 00:36:26.142
without stamping a presumption of guilt
all over himself?

790
00:36:27.018 --> 00:36:30.938
No. I think our half-white. half-black.
who-gives-a-shit-what-race-he-is son...

791
00:36:31.522 --> 00:36:34.650
The one who got 1470 on his SATs
and aced AP Physics.

792
00:36:34.734 --> 00:36:36.861
knows better than to commit
unforced errors in life

793
00:36:36.944 --> 00:36:38.196
by taking stupid risks.

794
00:36:39.113 --> 00:36:41.657
Especially. when he is on the cusp
of doing great things.

795
00:36:41.741 --> 00:36:44.493
I think he understands that.
like it or not.

796
00:36:45.203 --> 00:36:47.830
the way that you present yourself in life
has consequences.

797
00:36:47.914 --> 00:36:50.541
If you wear your pants
halfway down your ass

798
00:36:50.625 --> 00:36:52.501
and ghetto hair. then you got...

799
00:36:52.585 --> 00:36:54.545
Then you got no right to complain
when you walk by

800
00:36:54.587 --> 00:36:56.505
and a white lady clutches her purse?

801
00:36:57.048 --> 00:36:59.217
You got no right to complain
when you walk by

802
00:36:59.300 --> 00:37:00.843
and <i>any </i>lady clutches her purse.

803
00:37:00.927 --> 00:37:02.929
No. No. no. no. no. no. That is not... No.

804
00:37:03.012 --> 00:37:05.765
You are saying that associating
with other black kids

805
00:37:05.848 --> 00:37:07.266
is taking a stupid risk.

806
00:37:07.350 --> 00:37:09.190
Oh. come on. Kenny.
that's not what I'm saying.

807
00:37:09.227 --> 00:37:10.495
- Let me ask you.
- You know that!

808
00:37:10.519 --> 00:37:12.831
If this little asshole had told you
that Jamal was in a car

809
00:37:12.855 --> 00:37:15.983
with two white boys he barely knew.
would you be blaming him then?

810
00:37:16.067 --> 00:37:17.652
Would that be an unforced error?

811
00:37:17.735 --> 00:37:19.415
If I didn't know 'em. if I hadn't met 'em.

812
00:37:19.445 --> 00:37:21.447
black or white.
you're damn right. it would be.

813
00:37:21.530 --> 00:37:22.740
Scott...

814
00:37:23.241 --> 00:37:26.077
no matter how many privileges he's got.

815
00:37:26.619 --> 00:37:29.872
the world still looks at him
like it looks at me.

816
00:37:30.748 --> 00:37:31.582
not you.

817
00:37:31.666 --> 00:37:32.666
Oh. boy.

818
00:37:33.251 --> 00:37:35.419
I tell you.
I can see exactly what's been going on.

819
00:37:35.503 --> 00:37:38.172
I'm out of the house a few months.
and sure enough.

820
00:37:38.256 --> 00:37:39.382
you are filling his mind

821
00:37:39.465 --> 00:37:41.509
full of victimhood psychobabble.

822
00:37:41.592 --> 00:37:43.761
- Oh. you know what?
- "Pity me! Pity me!"

823
00:37:43.844 --> 00:37:45.530
- I've done nothing of the sort.
- [Scott] Yeah.

824
00:37:45.554 --> 00:37:47.056
Instead of pointing a finger at me.

825
00:37:47.139 --> 00:37:49.308
maybe you ought to be looking
in the mirror.

826
00:37:49.392 --> 00:37:50.476
Oh. this is my fault now?

827
00:37:50.559 --> 00:37:54.188
Well. you're the one who disappeared
at the pivotal moment in his life.

828
00:37:54.272 --> 00:37:55.314
Excuse me?

829
00:37:55.398 --> 00:37:57.275
You know exactly what I'm saying.

830
00:37:57.358 --> 00:37:59.819
I coached his baseball team for ten years.

831
00:37:59.902 --> 00:38:02.321
- Mmm.
- I went to every one of his concerts.

832
00:38:02.405 --> 00:38:03.990
Have I ever missed a banquet

833
00:38:04.073 --> 00:38:05.491
or a game or an event or a meet?

834
00:38:05.574 --> 00:38:08.136
- That's not what I'm talking about.
- What are you talking about?

835
00:38:08.160 --> 00:38:09.620
You walked out on him.

836
00:38:13.874 --> 00:38:14.792
I did not.

837
00:38:14.875 --> 00:38:16.294
- Yes. you did.
- Bullshit.

838
00:38:16.377 --> 00:38:17.420
- You did.
- No. I didn't.

839
00:38:17.503 --> 00:38:19.463
I'm sorry. but that is exactly what you...

840
00:38:19.547 --> 00:38:20.899
- [Scott] You know what?
- You did!

841
00:38:20.923 --> 00:38:22.133
You up and walked out on him.

842
00:38:22.216 --> 00:38:24.427
I didn't walk out on him.
I walked out on you.

843
00:38:31.517 --> 00:38:32.517
Oh.

844
00:38:32.935 --> 00:38:35.021
I didn't mean for it
to come out like that.

845
00:38:46.991 --> 00:38:47.991
I just...

846
00:38:48.784 --> 00:38:52.163
I'm so sick and tired of having
the same frickin' argument with you

847
00:38:52.246 --> 00:38:55.624
over and over and over again.
That is what I walked away from. Not...

848
00:38:56.751 --> 00:38:57.751
You know.

849
00:39:01.797 --> 00:39:03.758
Shit. Kenny. I'm sorry.

850
00:39:03.841 --> 00:39:05.092
- Stop.
- I didn't mean to...

851
00:39:05.176 --> 00:39:07.261
Just put the shovel down
and stop digging.

852
00:39:07.345 --> 00:39:10.473
Listen. J is on his way to being
a commissioned officer

853
00:39:10.556 --> 00:39:12.975
at one of the most elite institutions
on Earth.

854
00:39:13.059 --> 00:39:14.143
My job is done.

855
00:39:14.226 --> 00:39:15.644
He is a man now.

856
00:39:16.103 --> 00:39:17.355
A man I am so proud of.

857
00:39:17.438 --> 00:39:18.272
I know.

858
00:39:18.356 --> 00:39:22.610
So I cannot... I cannot have you telling me
I didn't do my job as a father.

859
00:39:23.110 --> 00:39:24.110
Okay.

860
00:39:26.864 --> 00:39:28.824
- I am not your father. Kendra.
- [Kendra] Okay.

861
00:39:28.908 --> 00:39:30.951
- That's what walking out looks like.
- All right.

862
00:39:31.035 --> 00:39:32.119
- So don't. Don't.
- Scott.

863
00:39:32.203 --> 00:39:33.954
- Please. Please.
- I said I get it.

864
00:39:37.375 --> 00:39:39.001
[thunder rumbling]

865
00:39:56.727 --> 00:39:57.727
Hey.

866
00:39:59.313 --> 00:40:00.648
- [sobbing]
- [Scott] Kenny.

867
00:40:04.276 --> 00:40:06.070
Everything's gonna be fine. all right?

868
00:40:06.153 --> 00:40:08.114
- Let's just try and relax.
- [sighs]

869
00:40:08.739 --> 00:40:09.740
[shudders]

870
00:40:14.578 --> 00:40:17.748
This time of night. I always get agitated.

871
00:40:19.583 --> 00:40:21.585
You have no idea.

872
00:40:22.545 --> 00:40:25.464
I'm usually awake about this time.

873
00:40:25.548 --> 00:40:29.051
I don't know I've had a sleep-filled night
since that boy was born.

874
00:40:35.808 --> 00:40:39.937
<i>Most nights. my eyes fire wide open
out of a sound sleep.</i>

875
00:40:40.354 --> 00:40:44.358
<i>Heart beating so hard
I feel it throbbing in my ears.</i>

876
00:40:44.733 --> 00:40:46.694
<i>Always right about this time.</i>

877
00:40:49.822 --> 00:40:52.032
<i>Too late to go back to sleep...</i>

878
00:40:53.951 --> 00:40:55.995
<i>too early to get on with the day.</i>

879
00:40:56.078 --> 00:40:58.080
[siren wailing]

880
00:40:58.873 --> 00:41:00.332
[thunder rumbling]

881
00:41:00.499 --> 00:41:05.004
<i>You... just snoring away.</i>

882
00:41:11.969 --> 00:41:15.097
Usually. I go stand
in the door to his room...

883
00:41:18.142 --> 00:41:20.102
<i>and listen to him breathe.</i>

884
00:41:22.980 --> 00:41:28.277
Sometimes I go in and...
touch the muscle on his neck.

885
00:41:30.863 --> 00:41:32.239
Or shoulder.

886
00:41:34.533 --> 00:41:36.744
<i>Stand there and bullshit myself.</i>

887
00:41:36.827 --> 00:41:41.832
<i>"Don't worry. Kendra.
he is big and powerful.</i>

888
00:41:41.916 --> 00:41:43.375
This world can't hurt him."

889
00:41:46.045 --> 00:41:51.425
Until that nagging feeling comes back.
and I dwell on how fragile he is.

890
00:41:53.427 --> 00:41:56.263
<i>And whatever nightmare
that has just woke me up.</i>

891
00:41:56.347 --> 00:42:01.101
<i>someone texting in an SUV
or an errant punch in a bar fight.</i>

892
00:42:01.477 --> 00:42:03.479
<i>a ruptured appendix</i>

893
00:42:03.562 --> 00:42:06.232
in some third world country. Most...

894
00:42:06.315 --> 00:42:09.610
Most mothers can sit there in the dark
and get rational.

895
00:42:09.693 --> 00:42:10.736
go back to sleep.

896
00:42:10.819 --> 00:42:15.908
But sometimes. in my nightmares.
I see nooses and crosses

897
00:42:15.991 --> 00:42:19.286
and white men with Brylcreem crew cuts.

898
00:42:33.092 --> 00:42:37.846
Last summer... when Jamal
wanted to drive with Jeff to Bonnaroo.

899
00:42:37.930 --> 00:42:41.725
- I was... I just...
- [Scott] No. look. J and I just thought

900
00:42:41.809 --> 00:42:44.037
you were a little over-the-top
with the mother hen thing.

901
00:42:44.061 --> 00:42:45.354
thinking he was too young.

902
00:42:45.437 --> 00:42:47.415
- Too young?
- [Scott] We disagreed and we moved on.

903
00:42:47.439 --> 00:42:49.119
Too young
had nothing to do with that shit.

904
00:42:49.191 --> 00:42:52.570
My granddaddy was fighting in Okinawa
when he was 17.

905
00:42:52.653 --> 00:42:53.862
Too <i>young?</i>

906
00:42:56.323 --> 00:42:57.449
It wasn't that.

907
00:42:58.742 --> 00:43:04.206
It was the prospect of him
driving through the Deep South.

908
00:43:06.041 --> 00:43:09.712
My son. alone with a white boy

909
00:43:09.795 --> 00:43:12.965
driving Sherman's March to the Sea
in reverse.

910
00:43:15.551 --> 00:43:19.763
[sniffles] Maybe he and Jeff stopped
to get gas in some little town

911
00:43:19.847 --> 00:43:21.432
'cause he doesn't know any better

912
00:43:21.515 --> 00:43:25.227
because we raised him to believe
that the world is full... [inhales sharply]

913
00:43:26.395 --> 00:43:27.855
full of goodness.

914
00:43:30.566 --> 00:43:35.279
And he starts batting his doe eyes
at some cute little white girl.

915
00:43:38.115 --> 00:43:40.534
Maybe the two of them walk
into a burger joint.

916
00:43:40.993 --> 00:43:43.203
happens to be an alt-right hangout.

917
00:43:46.665 --> 00:43:52.004
Maybe... some guy with a swastika
tattooed to his biceps

918
00:43:52.087 --> 00:43:54.298
had a little too much to drink. and...

919
00:43:55.883 --> 00:43:58.927
doesn't like the look...
[crying] of this boy

920
00:43:59.011 --> 00:44:02.389
who's poisoning
the country's racial purity.

921
00:44:03.307 --> 00:44:06.518
But the worst one.
the one that always comes back.

922
00:44:06.602 --> 00:44:10.439
is I see him getting stopped by a cop
for doing nothing in particular.

923
00:44:10.522 --> 00:44:13.192
<i>And I see ankle-high boots and...</i>

924
00:44:15.027 --> 00:44:16.070
badges...

925
00:44:19.073 --> 00:44:21.033
<i>and nightsticks.</i>

926
00:44:25.829 --> 00:44:28.332
And I think back on that night I was...

927
00:44:30.584 --> 00:44:32.294
five years old...

928
00:44:32.378 --> 00:44:36.632
and watched
my stoic mother doubled over.

929
00:44:37.174 --> 00:44:38.926
sobbing in the kitchen

930
00:44:39.009 --> 00:44:42.137
because Arthur McDuffie
had been beaten to death by the cops...

931
00:44:42.221 --> 00:44:44.682
[choking up]
...and they'd acquitted those cops.

932
00:44:49.061 --> 00:44:54.441
And you... [crying] were a little boy
asleep on the other side of town.

933
00:44:54.525 --> 00:44:56.819
dreaming of becoming one.

934
00:45:00.322 --> 00:45:01.949
[sobs] I'm scared.

935
00:45:02.032 --> 00:45:03.200
Don't be scared.

936
00:45:03.283 --> 00:45:04.118
- [Kendra] Yeah?
- Yeah.

937
00:45:04.201 --> 00:45:05.681
This is just some frivolous nonsense.

938
00:45:05.744 --> 00:45:07.624
They probably had
the music cranked up too loud.

939
00:45:07.705 --> 00:45:09.915
- You think?
- Yeah. you know how he likes to do.

940
00:45:10.749 --> 00:45:11.749
[scoffs]

941
00:45:12.626 --> 00:45:15.337
Or his buddies had a couple of beers
in the back seat. stupid shit.

942
00:45:15.421 --> 00:45:17.172
kids sowing wild oats.

943
00:45:19.800 --> 00:45:22.928
But let's not piss these people off. okay?

944
00:45:25.055 --> 00:45:26.055
Let's just...

945
00:45:27.266 --> 00:45:28.308
keep calm.

946
00:45:29.226 --> 00:45:31.770
Half an hour.
the three of us will be at Denny's...

947
00:45:33.605 --> 00:45:35.566
having a teachable moment.

948
00:45:42.030 --> 00:45:43.991
Have you talked to him recently?

949
00:45:44.450 --> 00:45:45.576
I talk to him every day.

950
00:45:45.659 --> 00:45:47.369
- Texting mostly. but...
- [Kendra] No.

951
00:45:47.453 --> 00:45:51.165
I mean. have you talked to him about...

952
00:45:51.248 --> 00:45:52.291
[Scott] About what?

953
00:45:53.333 --> 00:45:54.376
West Point.

954
00:45:55.627 --> 00:45:56.628
What about it?

955
00:45:57.254 --> 00:45:59.894
- I don't wanna get in the middle of this.
- [Scott] What about it?

956
00:46:01.550 --> 00:46:03.135
- Well. he's...
- [Scott] He's what?

957
00:46:03.218 --> 00:46:04.803
He's rethinking it.

958
00:46:06.388 --> 00:46:07.806
He's rethinking what?

959
00:46:10.017 --> 00:46:11.393
You should talk to him.

960
00:46:11.477 --> 00:46:12.770
About what. Kendra?

961
00:46:13.604 --> 00:46:14.604
[sighs]

962
00:46:15.230 --> 00:46:17.983
He's thinking about taking
the farm team contract.

963
00:46:18.817 --> 00:46:20.903
Or maybe seeing
where the guitar thing might go.

964
00:46:20.986 --> 00:46:21.987
Really?

965
00:46:22.070 --> 00:46:23.697
- Listen...
- Jesus Christ. Kenny. Again?

966
00:46:23.781 --> 00:46:26.092
It'd probably just be a deferment.
He's afraid to tell you.

967
00:46:26.116 --> 00:46:27.409
Yeah. well. he should be.

968
00:46:30.579 --> 00:46:31.747
I hope this wasn't your idea.

969
00:46:31.830 --> 00:46:33.791
- Okay. look.
- Are you encouraging this nonsense?

970
00:46:33.874 --> 00:46:36.335
He doesn't have the arm speed
to make it out of Double-A ball.

971
00:46:36.418 --> 00:46:37.961
He doesn't have the talent.

972
00:46:40.464 --> 00:46:42.716
A brutal reckoning that I. his father.

973
00:46:43.175 --> 00:46:45.385
not you. got to make with him. thank you.

974
00:46:45.469 --> 00:46:46.678
And the guitar?

975
00:46:47.346 --> 00:46:49.848
He's gonna. what?
Play the guitar. like. for a living?

976
00:46:49.932 --> 00:46:52.100
Just because you were too scared
to pursue your dreams.

977
00:46:52.184 --> 00:46:53.745
- don't take it out on him.
- Oh. please.

978
00:46:53.769 --> 00:46:54.929
Let him try while he's young.

979
00:46:55.562 --> 00:46:58.190
At worst.
he spends some time finding himself.

980
00:46:58.273 --> 00:47:00.313
Oh. sure.
You kick around trying to "find yourself."

981
00:47:00.359 --> 00:47:02.444
and before you know it.
you're a 40-year-old dude

982
00:47:02.528 --> 00:47:05.572
with a 150 IQ and no college degree.

983
00:47:07.115 --> 00:47:11.370
Then you're making. what. 450 a week
in a goddamn wedding cover band.

984
00:47:12.329 --> 00:47:13.831
Being hired by a guy

985
00:47:13.914 --> 00:47:16.124
who can afford to drop $100K
on the wedding

986
00:47:16.208 --> 00:47:18.252
because he didn't waste
ten years of his life

987
00:47:18.335 --> 00:47:20.879
pursuing his dreams of. you know.
the Olympic curling team.

988
00:47:20.963 --> 00:47:23.048
or writing the next great American novel.

989
00:47:23.131 --> 00:47:25.193
- That's not what I meant.
- The men in my family have

990
00:47:25.217 --> 00:47:27.469
served this country every generation
since they got here.

991
00:47:27.553 --> 00:47:29.304
He is not entitled
to break that tradition.

992
00:47:29.388 --> 00:47:30.639
- Scott.
- It's not an option.

993
00:47:30.722 --> 00:47:32.307
- End of discussion.
- [door closes]

994
00:47:32.391 --> 00:47:33.725
[Larkin] Sorry to interrupt.

995
00:47:34.101 --> 00:47:36.019
Coffee. No cream. no sugar.

996
00:47:36.103 --> 00:47:37.663
- [Scott] Thanks.
- [lock screen clicks]

997
00:47:37.729 --> 00:47:39.940
So. I got some more information for you.

998
00:47:40.023 --> 00:47:41.023
It's not a lot.

999
00:47:41.775 --> 00:47:43.777
I checked the computer intake log again.

1000
00:47:44.444 --> 00:47:45.571
[clears throat]

1001
00:47:46.655 --> 00:47:50.200
Your son was identified
as a vehicle occupant

1002
00:47:50.284 --> 00:47:52.119
in a traffic stop in your Lexus.

1003
00:47:52.202 --> 00:47:55.956
I also confirmed there were
two other black males

1004
00:47:56.039 --> 00:47:57.833
in the vehicle when it was stopped.

1005
00:47:57.916 --> 00:47:59.042
Why were they stopped?

1006
00:47:59.126 --> 00:48:00.669
The log's not really that specific.

1007
00:48:00.752 --> 00:48:02.713
The general "infraction" category
was checked off.

1008
00:48:02.796 --> 00:48:04.047
What does that mean?

1009
00:48:04.756 --> 00:48:06.967
It's just whatever
the patrol officer logged in

1010
00:48:07.050 --> 00:48:09.177
from his laptop in the patrol car.

1011
00:48:09.261 --> 00:48:10.470
He. like. checks off a box.

1012
00:48:10.554 --> 00:48:11.930
So this tells us nothing.

1013
00:48:12.014 --> 00:48:15.058
Well. it's not showing up
as a pursuit following felony.

1014
00:48:15.434 --> 00:48:17.728
a stolen car. BOLO.
You know. the really bad stuff...

1015
00:48:17.811 --> 00:48:19.271
- Okay.
- ...you can check off.

1016
00:48:19.354 --> 00:48:22.608
- [Scott] Who were the other boys?
- Yeah. I'm not allowed to. um...

1017
00:48:25.444 --> 00:48:28.113
Okay. this stays between us.
Badge to badge.

1018
00:48:31.033 --> 00:48:33.994
DaShawn Rolle and Jarvis Bell.

1019
00:48:34.077 --> 00:48:35.077
You know them?

1020
00:48:35.871 --> 00:48:38.665
Uh. Bell is a 20-year-old
with misdemeanor convictions.

1021
00:48:38.749 --> 00:48:39.875
He had an open warrant.

1022
00:48:39.958 --> 00:48:41.418
- For what?
- That I cannot tell you.

1023
00:48:41.501 --> 00:48:43.295
You see. Ken? Do you see what I'm saying?

1024
00:48:43.378 --> 00:48:45.213
Um. one other thing.

1025
00:48:45.297 --> 00:48:47.925
I gave your son's social media accounts
a quick look over.

1026
00:48:48.008 --> 00:48:51.470
Really? That's what you've been doing
while we're standing around in here?

1027
00:48:51.553 --> 00:48:54.640
Social media is. like. the first stop
in missing persons cases.

1028
00:48:54.723 --> 00:48:55.723
- Oh. please.
- Fact!

1029
00:48:59.019 --> 00:49:01.480
And that I did learn in a training video.

1030
00:49:05.776 --> 00:49:08.445
Your son posted something on Instagram.

1031
00:49:08.862 --> 00:49:12.199
A photo of a bumper sticker
on the back of your Lexus.

1032
00:49:14.076 --> 00:49:18.789
"Shoot cops with your camera phone
whenever they make a bust."

1033
00:49:19.581 --> 00:49:21.333
- Excuse me?
- That is what it says.

1034
00:49:21.416 --> 00:49:23.043
- "Shoot cops"?
- Yeah. yeah.

1035
00:49:23.126 --> 00:49:26.046
And those words
were in. like. huge letters. okay?

1036
00:49:26.129 --> 00:49:28.399
- I think you're mistaken.
- The rest of it in little fonts.

1037
00:49:28.423 --> 00:49:30.943
so all anyone who wasn't two feet away
from the bumper could see

1038
00:49:30.968 --> 00:49:32.636
is a Lexus that says. "Shoot cops."

1039
00:49:32.719 --> 00:49:35.180
No... [chuckling] No. not my son.

1040
00:49:35.263 --> 00:49:36.515
[sniffles]

1041
00:49:38.725 --> 00:49:39.725
Afraid so.

1042
00:49:53.573 --> 00:49:54.866
"Shoot cops."

1043
00:49:54.950 --> 00:49:56.743
Shoot people just trying to do their jobs.

1044
00:49:56.827 --> 00:49:58.012
- That's all you can see?
- Yup.

1045
00:49:58.036 --> 00:50:00.330
- Jesus Christ.
- Shoot people with wives and kids.

1046
00:50:00.414 --> 00:50:01.331
Son of a bitch.

1047
00:50:01.415 --> 00:50:04.584
Just shoot 'em 'cause you're part
of the revolution or whatever. I guess.

1048
00:50:04.668 --> 00:50:05.669
- Kendra.
- What?

1049
00:50:05.752 --> 00:50:08.130
- That car is registered in my name.
- God...

1050
00:50:08.213 --> 00:50:11.299
This isn't about us. remember?
Our son is in police custody.

1051
00:50:11.383 --> 00:50:14.469
Our son has a bumper sticker
on his car that says. "Shoot cops."

1052
00:50:14.553 --> 00:50:16.114
- My son. I'm the cops.
- [Kendra] Scott.

1053
00:50:16.138 --> 00:50:19.224
- God damn it. I'm the cops!
- This is about a camera phone.

1054
00:50:20.517 --> 00:50:21.351
Jesus. Scott!

1055
00:50:21.435 --> 00:50:23.562
Right now. I couldn't care less
about you and him

1056
00:50:23.645 --> 00:50:25.022
and your goddamn thin blue line.

1057
00:50:25.105 --> 00:50:26.481
I care about finding our son.

1058
00:50:26.565 --> 00:50:28.442
Did you know about this? Had you seen it?

1059
00:50:28.525 --> 00:50:30.645
Kenny. please tell me
that you didn't know about this.

1060
00:50:30.694 --> 00:50:32.863
- Please tell me that you didn't...
- Listen to me.

1061
00:50:34.239 --> 00:50:36.867
There are three black kids in his school.

1062
00:50:37.242 --> 00:50:40.037
Three out of 400 and something.

1063
00:50:40.120 --> 00:50:42.581
And the other two are dating each other.

1064
00:50:42.664 --> 00:50:44.100
- He's...
- Oh. no. I totally get it.

1065
00:50:44.124 --> 00:50:45.500
Being one of the only black kids

1066
00:50:45.584 --> 00:50:47.753
at the most expensive prep school
in the city...

1067
00:50:48.587 --> 00:50:50.756
versus being a black kid at.
you know. MLK Senior.

1068
00:50:50.839 --> 00:50:52.900
where you gotta go through metal detectors
every day.

1069
00:50:52.924 --> 00:50:56.344
that entitles you to put a bumper sticker
on your Lexus

1070
00:50:56.428 --> 00:50:59.431
that says. "Shoot the stupid dumbass
who bought me this car."

1071
00:50:59.514 --> 00:51:02.100
He is grappling with a lot right now.

1072
00:51:02.934 --> 00:51:04.936
- He's depressed.
- Oh. Jesus.

1073
00:51:05.020 --> 00:51:06.063
He's confused.

1074
00:51:06.146 --> 00:51:09.316
Bullshit. Look. I'm sorry to be venting
like this in front of you.

1075
00:51:09.399 --> 00:51:11.151
Oh. no. listen. I totally hear you.

1076
00:51:11.234 --> 00:51:12.736
Where is Jamal now?

1077
00:51:13.320 --> 00:51:16.031
What I just told you.
that is all that is in the system.

1078
00:51:16.114 --> 00:51:17.991
and I wasn't even supposed
to tell you that.

1079
00:51:18.075 --> 00:51:19.242
I'm really supposed to wait

1080
00:51:19.326 --> 00:51:21.411
for this Lieutenant Stokes guy
to get here.

1081
00:51:22.287 --> 00:51:25.332
But. I tell you what.
I will go and check the computer again.

1082
00:51:25.415 --> 00:51:27.175
see if someone might have
logged something in

1083
00:51:27.209 --> 00:51:28.460
in the last few minutes.

1084
00:51:30.796 --> 00:51:31.922
[Kendra] You know what?

1085
00:51:32.047 --> 00:51:34.132
I sat around here almost half an hour.

1086
00:51:34.216 --> 00:51:36.343
You couldn't tell me a damn thing.

1087
00:51:36.718 --> 00:51:38.303
Except for maybe how to go on

1088
00:51:38.386 --> 00:51:40.847
a self-guided. Jim Crow tour
through the building...

1089
00:51:40.931 --> 00:51:44.810
And then as soon as my husband shows up.
my white husband.

1090
00:51:44.893 --> 00:51:46.978
suddenly you are as helpful as can be.

1091
00:51:47.062 --> 00:51:48.438
- [Scott] Kendra!
- Why is that?

1092
00:51:49.314 --> 00:51:52.025
Do you not want me to go look
at the computer again?

1093
00:51:52.109 --> 00:51:54.194
- [Kendra huffs]
- If you wouldn't mind too much.

1094
00:51:54.277 --> 00:51:56.113
I'm sorry. I didn't get your first name.

1095
00:51:56.947 --> 00:51:57.781
Paul.

1096
00:51:57.864 --> 00:52:00.325
Paul. if you wouldn't mind.
we'd really appreciate it.

1097
00:52:01.451 --> 00:52:02.451
Sure thing.

1098
00:52:04.079 --> 00:52:05.956
- Refill?
- That'd be great.

1099
00:52:15.132 --> 00:52:16.132
"That'd be great."

1100
00:52:17.259 --> 00:52:18.844
You know what else would be great?

1101
00:52:18.927 --> 00:52:20.929
If you took my side at some point.

1102
00:52:21.012 --> 00:52:22.264
Damn it. Kendra.

1103
00:52:22.347 --> 00:52:24.349
You're so goddamn nice to him.
it's making me sick.

1104
00:52:24.432 --> 00:52:27.120
- "Shoot cops"? For Christ's sake.
- That's why you're kissing this guy's ass?

1105
00:52:27.144 --> 00:52:29.312
No. I'm ready to put my fist
through the goddamn wall.

1106
00:52:29.396 --> 00:52:30.581
Put yourself in Jamal's place.

1107
00:52:30.605 --> 00:52:33.150
- Oh. give me a break.
- No! Just for one minute.

1108
00:52:33.233 --> 00:52:36.278
put yourself in your son's place.

1109
00:52:42.242 --> 00:52:44.411
He is the only black person

1110
00:52:44.494 --> 00:52:47.122
most of those little white kids
at his school know.

1111
00:52:48.081 --> 00:52:49.166
Most of 'em...

1112
00:52:50.500 --> 00:52:53.628
only black people
they've ever exchanged two words with

1113
00:52:53.712 --> 00:52:57.382
are the Jamaican hospice woman
who wipes bubbie's ass.

1114
00:52:57.757 --> 00:53:00.385
and the people
at some Habitat for Humanity house

1115
00:53:00.468 --> 00:53:02.188
they helped build
just so they had something

1116
00:53:02.220 --> 00:53:03.860
to put on their application to Princeton.

1117
00:53:03.889 --> 00:53:05.741
- Look. I get that.
- You have to understand. Scott.

1118
00:53:05.765 --> 00:53:07.517
Jamal is going through...

1119
00:53:15.817 --> 00:53:17.027
an awakening.

1120
00:53:17.527 --> 00:53:19.046
- An awakening? To what?
- [Kendra] Yes.

1121
00:53:19.070 --> 00:53:20.155
To this.

1122
00:53:39.007 --> 00:53:40.007
Okay.

1123
00:53:41.718 --> 00:53:43.470
And? [exhales]

1124
00:53:44.221 --> 00:53:45.221
And...

1125
00:53:46.598 --> 00:53:48.683
Philando Castile.

1126
00:53:50.644 --> 00:53:52.020
And Eric Garner.

1127
00:53:53.355 --> 00:53:55.023
And Tamir Rice.

1128
00:53:56.107 --> 00:53:57.943
Every time it happens.

1129
00:53:58.026 --> 00:54:00.779
he feels the world
close in on him a little.

1130
00:54:00.862 --> 00:54:03.073
And it's coming at him from both sides

1131
00:54:03.156 --> 00:54:07.369
because all of his white friends
think he represents the entire race.

1132
00:54:07.452 --> 00:54:11.706
It's not like if he was at a school
with other black kids he could lean on.

1133
00:54:11.790 --> 00:54:14.459
He is the one all the white kids look to.

1134
00:54:14.542 --> 00:54:17.796
There is <i>immense</i> pressure on him to...

1135
00:54:18.505 --> 00:54:21.758
[chuckles] I'll tell you what he calls it.
"the face of the race."

1136
00:54:23.635 --> 00:54:27.847
That's what he says.
"I feel like I am the face of the race."

1137
00:54:28.848 --> 00:54:30.809
- He told you this?
- [Kendra] Many times.

1138
00:54:32.310 --> 00:54:34.271
He never said anything like that to me.

1139
00:54:38.149 --> 00:54:39.985
Baby. look at you...

1140
00:54:40.652 --> 00:54:43.196
and look at me
and reckon why that might be.

1141
00:54:48.535 --> 00:54:50.870
When these men get shot down.

1142
00:54:50.954 --> 00:54:53.331
he can feel their ghosts.

1143
00:54:55.333 --> 00:54:57.002
That bumper sticker was...

1144
00:54:58.295 --> 00:54:59.587
Was what?

1145
00:55:01.381 --> 00:55:02.966
No. really. I... I...

1146
00:55:04.301 --> 00:55:06.469
- I want to understand.
- [sobbing]

1147
00:55:07.012 --> 00:55:08.179
[groans]

1148
00:55:09.472 --> 00:55:10.640
[chuckling]

1149
00:55:15.228 --> 00:55:19.316
Can you see that Jamal
is also right. here?

1150
00:55:20.775 --> 00:55:23.236
Filming cops is all these kids have.

1151
00:55:23.320 --> 00:55:25.238
It is their last line of defense.

1152
00:55:25.322 --> 00:55:28.867
Shit. God forbid I'm stopped.
it's mine too.

1153
00:55:28.950 --> 00:55:31.077
That is the world we live in.

1154
00:55:31.161 --> 00:55:32.662
Whether you get it or not.

1155
00:55:36.082 --> 00:55:38.209
[thunder rumbling]

1156
00:55:41.338 --> 00:55:42.881
No. I get it. I do.

1157
00:55:45.216 --> 00:55:46.216
I get it.

1158
00:55:48.386 --> 00:55:49.386
I just...

1159
00:55:52.223 --> 00:55:55.143
He still should've known
where this kind of thing can lead.

1160
00:55:55.226 --> 00:55:56.226
Where?

1161
00:55:56.644 --> 00:55:58.438
Here? [sniffles]

1162
00:55:58.521 --> 00:55:59.521
- Tonight?
- Yeah.

1163
00:55:59.564 --> 00:56:01.004
- Because of a bumper sticker?
- Yes.

1164
00:56:01.066 --> 00:56:02.746
You really think
that's what this is about?

1165
00:56:02.776 --> 00:56:04.253
- Sure didn't help.
- A bumper sticker?

1166
00:56:04.277 --> 00:56:06.821
Look. if I'm a cop rolling down the street
at 2:00 a.m..

1167
00:56:06.905 --> 00:56:08.782
and it's a close call on probable cause...

1168
00:56:08.865 --> 00:56:10.867
The bumper sticker would push you
over the edge?

1169
00:56:10.950 --> 00:56:12.369
- You bet.
- Oh... [chuckling]

1170
00:56:12.452 --> 00:56:14.913
Especially. if after I make
a warning stop.

1171
00:56:14.996 --> 00:56:18.208
I got some uppity asshole
lecturing me about his rights.

1172
00:56:18.291 --> 00:56:19.584
[whispering] Son of a bitch.

1173
00:56:20.001 --> 00:56:21.002
What?

1174
00:56:23.171 --> 00:56:24.172
"Uppity"?

1175
00:56:25.965 --> 00:56:27.759
- Oh. come on.
- Is that what you just said?

1176
00:56:27.842 --> 00:56:29.403
- [Scott] Kendra. please.
- Unbelievable.

1177
00:56:29.427 --> 00:56:30.780
- [Scott] Jesus Christ.
- From you?

1178
00:56:30.804 --> 00:56:32.097
I don't even know what to say.

1179
00:56:32.180 --> 00:56:35.642
God damn it. don't make this about
how I tripped on some coded word fossil.

1180
00:56:40.897 --> 00:56:43.858
I cannot have J lapsing into a life

1181
00:56:43.942 --> 00:56:46.569
where he makes excuses for himself
all the time. I won't.

1182
00:56:46.653 --> 00:56:49.239
And I won't have him walking around
apologizing for who he is.

1183
00:56:49.322 --> 00:56:51.950
- No one is asking him to do that.
- Yes. they are.

1184
00:56:55.745 --> 00:56:58.081
"Keep your hands on the wheel. boy.
Look straight ahead.

1185
00:56:58.164 --> 00:57:00.125
Don't make any sudden moves.

1186
00:57:00.208 --> 00:57:04.087
Wouldn't want to make the man
in the bulletproof vest nervous

1187
00:57:04.170 --> 00:57:08.383
when he walks up to your window
pointing a glock at your head."

1188
00:57:12.220 --> 00:57:14.013
Your father ever tell you that?

1189
00:57:14.931 --> 00:57:17.475
- He never had to.
- You're goddamn right. he didn't.

1190
00:57:21.938 --> 00:57:24.482
- [rain pattering]
- [thunder rumbling]

1191
00:57:32.574 --> 00:57:33.867
Look. Kenny.

1192
00:57:38.455 --> 00:57:41.458
I'm as eager to sort this out as you are.
He is my son. too.

1193
00:57:43.001 --> 00:57:44.794
I just don't think that. you know.

1194
00:57:45.503 --> 00:57:48.882
lecturing these people
on Black Lives Matter is gonna help.

1195
00:57:50.467 --> 00:57:51.801
Let's try...

1196
00:57:53.219 --> 00:57:55.138
catching flies with honey. okay?

1197
00:57:55.221 --> 00:57:57.098
Maybe they need a little lecture.

1198
00:57:58.266 --> 00:58:01.186
They sure fittin' to get one
when I sue their asses.

1199
00:58:01.686 --> 00:58:02.854
Look. alls I'm saying...

1200
00:58:02.937 --> 00:58:03.937
<i>all...</i>

1201
00:58:05.231 --> 00:58:06.483
all I'm saying...

1202
00:58:06.858 --> 00:58:09.068
is let's give these people
the benefit of the doubt

1203
00:58:09.152 --> 00:58:12.071
and not act like we're
in some ass-backwards Klan county

1204
00:58:12.155 --> 00:58:14.491
in South Carolina.
This is Miami. for God's sake.

1205
00:58:14.574 --> 00:58:17.327
Where my black. PhD-having ass

1206
00:58:17.410 --> 00:58:20.622
still has to drive down
something called "South Dixie Highway"

1207
00:58:20.705 --> 00:58:21.998
to get to work every day.

